<dt>Volunteer Opportunities</dt>
<dd>We invite you to take a look at our new web page on <a href="http://www.rwuc.org/volunteer.html">Volunteer Opportunities</a> at Robertson-Wesley. We believe that everyone has a gift to share and everyone is called to discipleship.</dd>


<dt>Community Dinner</dt>
<dd>Every second Saturday of the month a group of dedicated volunteers prepare a hot meal for the community. The dinner is at 5:00 pm. There is no cost to attend.
<strong>Next Community Dinner is Saturday, March 12.</strong></dd>

<dt>Scripture Reflection Tuesdays</dt>
<dd><strong>Every Tuesday &middot; 12:10 pm</strong>
<br>Join Rev. Karen Bridges in the Club Room over lunch to reflect on the scripture passages for the upcoming Sunday. Bring a bible and a journal, or simply yourself! Come when you can and bring your lunch if you wish.
<br>For full details visit the <a href="http://www.rwuc.org/scriptureReflections.html">Scripture Reflections webpage</a></dd>
</dd> 


<dt>Mission and Outreach Pod Conversation</dt>
<dd><strong>Mar 13 &middot; Sun &middot; 12 pm</strong>
<br>The Mission and Outreach POD coordinator Jennifer Dixon, and Rev. Karen Bridges invite you, your friends and family to join an open discussion about how we as a church are called to participating in our city, and use our space as, a place of welcoming, warmth, and unconditional love for its residents and community at large. We hope to see you all there! Bring your thoughts and ideas and let's talk!
</dd>


<dt>St. Patrick's Dinner</dt>
<dd><strong>Mar 19 &middot; Sat &middot; 5:30 pm</strong>
<br> Meet your neighbours and friends over a delicious supper of beef or lamb stew, little potatoes, coleslaw, homemade buns, dessert, beverages and a cash bar.  There will also be draws for door prizes.
Tickets are $ 20.00 for adults, children 5-11 years $ 5.00, and youth 12-15 years are $10.00.  Tickets may be purchased through the church office, and at the door.
</dd>


<dt>Spiritual Practices</dt>
<dd><strong>Mar 20 &middot; 7 - 8:30 pm</strong>
<br>We will begin Holy Week on the eve of Palm Sunday by inviting people to come and engage in some silent spiritual prayerful practices. This is a self-guided practice that will provide you with a space to reconnect with God. There will be a variety of stations set up in Memorial Hall with instructions indicating what you can do. Some examples of the stations are a Labyrinth Walk, Meditation on images, sculpting scriptures, writing a letter to God just to name a few.
<br>For full details visit the <a href="http://www.rwuc.org/easter.html">Lent & Easter webpage</a></dd>
</dd> 


<dt>The Big Apple!</dt>
<dd>Incredible news to announce!  The R-W Choir, along with the Knox-Metropolitan Choir has been invited to sing in Carnegie Hall in New York City - in June 2016!</dd>

