Both classes are graciously offered free of charge by the instructors. The classes are open to the community.
</dd>

<dt>"Ask Me" People Training</dt>
<dd><strong>2014 Aug 24<br>Sunday at 11:45 am to 2:00 pm<br>Room 11</strong>
<br>Here at Robertson-Wesley we have people visiting our church all the time, and the reality is that this church is big, there are lots of things going on, and lots of things to 
discover if you are new, and even if you have been here for a long time, to the scene.
<br>Part of our new strategy to be a welcoming and inclusive community is to have people available on Sunday to answer questions and help people find their way within our midst so that people feel welcome. Fear not! We are not looking for experts, we are looking for people who enjoy meeting people, who enjoy having conversations and helping others, and who are passionate about this church.
<br>We know that availability differs for most people, so the more people involved the better! Please join us for this training session and then decide if this is something you would like to do. 
<br>All ages are welcome and it doesn't matter if you have been at this church for 3 months or 30 years. If you have any questions feel free to talk with Rev. Karen Bridges
</dd>


<dt>All is Bright Festival</dt>
<dd><strong>2015 Nov 21, Saturday, 3 - 8pm on 124 Street</strong><br>
For the past 3 years the 124St. Business Association has been putting on a winter festival that seeks to brighten up our neighbourhood and bring the people of this area together. The street will be closed off from 3-8pm. There will be a sleigh rides, activities for children and some for adults, a beer gardens, a stage with live entertainment, some of our choir members will be caroling and children can get their picture taken with Santa Clause. There will be a lighting ceremony at 6:30pm. From 3-6:30pm at Robertson-United Church we will be inviting people to come and <strong>make lanterns</strong> with some of our Artists-in-residence. In the club room there will be a gathering of people for <strong>Craft and Draught</strong>. People will be invited to knit and have a beer together. Then from 7-9pm there will be a <strong>Java Jam Coffee House</strong> in Memorial Hall featuring some wonderful local singers and artists. This is a free event and we hope that you will come out and join in the fun. We are seeking volunteers to greet people at the door of the church, people to help with beverage preparation, lantern making assistants and some people to help with clean up. 
<br><strong>A sign-up sheet is in Memorial Hall.</strong> 
For a complete schedule and latest updates visit <a href="http://www.124street.ca/all-is-bright/">the festival web page.</a></dd>


